data.title: A Day to Remember - Re-Entry Lyrics & Meanings
data.meta_description: Re-Entry Lyrics & Meanings: [Verse 1] / These nights are long here in my cage / Everyone says to act my age / It's been so long since I've felt my back / Replayin' mistakes over in my head /  / [Pre-Chorus 1] / Sleeping in this coffin, I keep wakin' up / I don't drink too much, I just drink enough /  / [Chorus] / I just wanna go / I just wanna go home / I just wanna go / I just wanna go home /  / [Verse 2] / A three piece suit's like a three piece cage / The cubicle of our modern age / That feels so foreign, alien like me / Breakin' through this re-entry anxiety /  / [Pre-Chorus 2] / Two week decompression then I get that itch / Gotta pack it up and start again /  / [Chorus] / I just wanna go / I just wanna go home / I just wanna go / I just wanna go homе /  / [Refrain] / And I don't know when I'll be back again / Caught a cabin fevеr that never ends / And I don't know when I'll be back again / Caught a cabin fever that never ends / And I don't know when I'll be back again / Caught a cabin fever that never ends / And I don't know when I'll be back again / Caught a cabin fever that never ends / And I just wanna go home /  / [Chorus] / I just wanna go / I just wanna go home / I just wanna go / I just wanna go home / I just wanna go home / I just wanna go home
data.text:
[Verse 1]

These nights are long here in my cage

Everyone says to act my age

It's been so long since I've felt my back

Replayin' mistakes over in my head

[Pre-Chorus 1]

Sleeping in this coffin, I keep wakin' up

I don't drink too much, I just drink enough

[Chorus]

I just wanna go

I just wanna go home

I just wanna go

I just wanna go home

[Verse 2]

A three piece suit's like a three piece cage

The cubicle of our modern age

That feels so foreign, alien like me

Breakin' through this re-entry anxiety

[Pre-Chorus 2]

Two week decompression then I get that itch

Gotta pack it up and start again

[Chorus]

I just wanna go

I just wanna go home

I just wanna go

I just wanna go homе

[Refrain]

And I don't know when I'll be back again

Caught a cabin fevеr that never ends

And I don't know when I'll be back again

Caught a cabin fever that never ends

And I don't know when I'll be back again

Caught a cabin fever that never ends

And I don't know when I'll be back again

Caught a cabin fever that never ends

And I just wanna go home

[Chorus]

I just wanna go

I just wanna go home

I just wanna go

I just wanna go home

I just wanna go home

I just wanna go home
